==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Eradicate
<hw>E*rad"i*cate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Eradicated</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Eradicating</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>eradicatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>eradicare</ets> to eradicate;
<ets>e</ets> out + <ets>radix</ets>, <ets>radicis</ets>, root. See
<er>Radical</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To pluck up by the roots; to
root up; <as>as, an oak tree <ex>eradicated</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To root out; to destroy utterly; to extirpate;
<as>as, to <ex>eradicate</ex> diseases, or errors</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This, although now an old an inveterate evil, might be
<qex>eradicated</qex> by vigorous treatment.</q>
<rj><qau>Southey.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To extirpate; root out; exterminate; destroy;
annihilate.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Eradication</ent>⟦br⟧
